On Sun, 2 Jan 2005 mccomas(-at-)intercom.net wrote:

> Every now and then, someone posts on the subject of towing a Type II.  I'm
> looking at a tow bar ~400 miles from here, wondering how to get it transported
> at reasonable cost.  FedX is quoting $85 and the seller would need to make a
> box for it.  Questions:
>
> (1) Does anyone have favorable experience shipping an object like this, via
> FedX Ground, or maybe UPS, or other shipping services?

In addition to the one-word answer (Greyhound) there is a two-word answer
as well...  Parcel Post.  The USPS will accept and deliver the most
unusual things, up to and including live animals!  If you can get a label
on it, they will take it.

OOK!
